$Id: README,v 1.2 2002/07/07 20:27:46 mardan Exp $


Description:
-----------------------------------------------------------
Netstat-nat is a small program written in C. It displays 
NATed connections, created by netfilter/iptables from the 
>2.4.x linux kernel. The program reads its information from 
'/proc/net/ip_conntrack', which is the temporary conntrack-
storage from netfilter. (http://netfilter.samba.org/)

-----------------------------------------------------------


Compiling:
-----------------------------------------------------------
gcc netstat-nat.c -o netstat-nat
strip netstat-nat

-----------------------------------------------------------


Usage:
-----------------------------------------------------------
netstat-nat -h		: displays help
netstat-nat -n		: displays NATed connections
			  without hostname-resolving.
netstat-nat -p tcp | udp | icmp
			: diplays NATed connections with
			  protocol selection.
netstat-nat -s <source-host> :prints only connections by 
			      NATed IP/hostname
-----------------------------------------------------------


